SLS SwZTJ FGwzt ukgoS" href="/ShowUserReviews-g60750-d482152-r989397956-Petco_Park-San_Diego_California.html"><span __id__="4916" class="yCeTE">Behind The Scenes Alcatraz</span></a><span __id__="4921" class="yCeTE">Recently, I had the incredible opportunity to take a journey on the California Zephyr train from Chicago to San Francisco. Known as one of the most scenic train routes in the United States, the Zephyr winds through breathtaking landscapes, from the majestic Rocky Mountains to the arid beauty of the Nevada deserts. The relaxing pace of train travel gave me time to soak in the views and appreciate the unique charm of this cross-country adventure.Upon arriving in California, one of the highlights of my trip was taking the behind-the-scenes tour of Alcatraz Island. This tour offered a deeper dive into the history and mysteries of the infamous former prison. Unlike the standard tours, the behind-the-scenes experience granted access to areas usually closed to the public, such as hidden tunnels, the prison’s old workshops, and the hospital ward.The tour guide was incredibly knowledgeable and brought the stories of Alcatraz to life, sharing fascinating anecdotes about its most notorious inmates and the daring escape attempts that have captivated imaginations for decades. Walking through the dimly lit corridors and seeing the cells up close was both eerie and enlightening. It gave me a newfound respect for the challenges faced by those who lived and worked on the island.What stood out most to me was learning about the island’s broader history, including its time as a military fortress and its significance to Native American activists during the occupation in the late 1960s. The layers of history made the visit even more enriching.I would highly recommend the Alcatraz behind-the-scenes tour to anyone visiting San Francisco. It’s an unforgettable experience that combines history, intrigue, and stunning views of the Bay Area. Pairing this tour with the scenic Zephyr train ride made for a truly memorable adventure.</span><button __id__="4931" class="UikNM _G B- _S _W _T c G_ wSSLS wnNQG" type="button"><span __id__="4932" class="biGQs _P XWJSj Wb">Read more</span></button><a __id__="4938" class="BMQDV _F Gv wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt suezE" href="/Attraction_Review-g60750-d482152-Reviews-Petco_Park-San_Diego_California.html#REVIEWS">Review of: Petco Park</a><div __id__="4940" class="biGQs _P pZUbB ncFvv osNWb">Written January 15, 2025</div><div __id__="4941" class="biGQs _P pZUbB mowmC osNWb">This review is the subjective opinion of a Tripadvisor member and not of Tripadvisor LLC. Tripadvisor performs checks on reviews.</div></li><li __id__="4943" class="GDjZb Fg I _u"><a __id__="4961" class="BMQDV _F Gv wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt ukgoS" href="/Profile/theresehL3040ZY">Therese H</a><span __id__="4964" class="">4 contributions</span><button __id__="4966" aria-label="Click to add helpful vote" class="BrOJk u j z _F wSSLS HuPlH Vonfv" type="button"><span __id__="4970" class="biGQs _P FwFXZ">0</span></button><button __id__="4973" aria-label="Open Options Menu" class="BrOJk u j z _F wSSLS HuPlH Vonfv" type="button"></button><title __id__="4978">5.0 of 5 bubbles</title><a __id__="4985" class="BMQDV _F Gv wSSLS SwZTJ FGwzt ukgoS" href="/ShowUserReviews-g60750-d274103-r994247862-Little_Italy-San_Diego_California.html"><span __id__="4986" class="yCeTE">Great Place to Visit for Foodies</span></a><span __id__="4991" class="yCeTE">I visited Little Italy during a trip to San Diego at the end of January 2025.  I went to Vincenzo's for dinner one night and Civico's for lunch the next day.  Both were fabulous!! The food was EXCELLENT at both places.  Little Italy is such a vibrant and exciting area!  If you visit, you have to stop at Salt &amp; Straw for some awesome ice cream also!  Very unique flavors.  I wanted to go through the farmers market on Saturday, but we were short on time.  Would love to come back some day and eat at more restaurants in Little Italy.